15/11/2005
PRESEVO, Serbia-Montenegro -- Bilingualism will be introduced in the judicial and educational sectors in Presevo as part of efforts to resolve interethnic issues in southern Serbia. 
On Monday (14 November), Serbian government representatives, OSCE officials and local authorities met in Presevo. 
Serbian Justice Minister Zoran Stojkovic says the agreement envisions the use of Albanian in parallel to Serbian in the municipal courts of Presevo and Bujanovac. 
In addition, more ethnic Albanians would be hired in the state judiciary. 
(Tanjug, Beta - 14/11/05)
